===Etymology 1===
The long form of {{m|ja|我|tr=a}}. Compound of {{m|ja|我|tr=a}} and suffix {{m|ja|れ|tr=re}}.

====Alternative forms====
* {{l|ja|吾}}

====Pronunciation====
{{ja-pron|acc=h}}

====Pronoun====
{{ja-pos|pronoun}}

# {{ja-def|我}} {{lb|ja|archaic}} ''[[first-person]] [[personal pronoun]]'': [[I]], [[me]]

===Etymology 2===
From older ''[[かれ|kare]]'' → ''are''.

====Pronunciation====
{{ja-pron|acc=h}}

====Pronoun====
{{ja-pos|pronoun}}

# {{ja-def|彼れ}} ''([[deictically]])'' [[that]] one over there (far from the speaker and the addressee)
# {{ja-def|彼れ}} ''([[anaphorically]])'' [[that]] one we both know (both the speaker and the addressee know)

=====Usage notes=====
* Indicates something far off, removed from both speaker and addressee. Contrast with [[それ|sore]], indicating something removed from the speaker but closer to the addressee.

=====Alternative forms=====
* {{l|ja|彼}}

